## **How to run gcsim’s optimizer code** **(as well as Athena’s sim optimizer automation code)**

**In GitHub**

1. Go to gcsim’s GitHub: [https://github.com/genshinsim/gcsim/releases](https://github.com/genshinsim/gcsim/releases)   
2. In **Assets**, click one of the **gcsim.exe** packs to download them. Choose the pack that matches your OS.  
3. Go to Athena’s GitHub: [https://github.com/Athenaxdd/gcsim\_run\_config](https://github.com/Athenaxdd/gcsim_run_config)  
4. Download the zip folder with the code via the green **\<\> Code** button

![][image1]

**In Python**

1. Go to the Python website: [https://www.python.org/downloads/](https://www.python.org/downloads/)  
2. Download the latest Python version (if you haven’t already)  
5. In the Python setup, click **Modify** and ensure the box for **pip** is checked. Install this modification.

![][image2]  
**Setting up the gcsim Folder**

1. Extract or unzip the contents of the **gcsim.exe folder**  
2. Place the **.exe** file in its own folder, separate from the rest of your downloaded files  
3. In this **new gcsim folder**, right click and open a **.txt** file via Notepad or a similar app  
4. Copy paste your desired sim config into the **.txt** file. Save the file as **\[  test  \]** or some similar, easy name  
5. Back in the gcsim folder with the .exe and .txt file, right click to **Open Terminal**  
6. In Terminal, run the following command  
   * \[  ./gcsim.exe \-c test.txt \-s \-substatOptimFull  \]  
   * **Note that this command will only run if the .exe file and .txt files have matching names**  
   * In this case, this command runs only if the files are specifically named \[  gcsim.exe  \] and \[  test.txt  \], but both the command and/or the file names can be altered to match  
7. If the information in the config is complete, the Terminal should begin to optimize the sim and load the optimized sim on your browser

What the command should look like when run in Terminal:  
![][image3]

The above information is all you need to optimize a sim. However, for guide calculations, you need to run many sims for various weapons and artifacts. Athena’s sim optimizer automation makes this process much simpler.

**Setting up Athena’s Folder and the gcsim Folder**

1. Extract or unzip the contents of **Athena’s gcsim folder**  
2. Place its contents into a folder **that is separate** from your pre-existing gcsim folder  
3. In your **new folder** dedicated to Athena’s code, copy the following files into your **gcsim folder** that contains gcsim.exe  
   * config folder  
   * config optimization folder  
   * viewer\_gz folder  
   * run\_optimizer\_full.bat  
4. Copy paste your desired config into **\[  config.txt  \]**  
5. Return to the **Athena folder**; Open Terminal and run either one of two commands depending on your sim needs  
   * \[  python auto\_weapons.py  \]  
   * \[  python artifacts.py  \]   
6. Input the gear and character names according to the prompts given in Terminal (making sure to write in **all lowercase**)  
   * When entering the name of the script file, enter **\[  config.txt  \]**, as it contains your sim config  
7. Once finished, run **\[  python generate\_batch.py  \]** in the same Terminal, also following the prompts given  
   * The name of the output file should be **“batch”**

Here is an example of the Terminal **run in the Athena folder**:  
![][image4]

8. When both Python commands have been run in the Terminal in the Athena folder, you should have **two new files: an output.txt file and an output folder**

The output.txt file should be named “batch\_output.txt” because that is the name entered upon batch generation. The output folder name is titled “bennett sword” because that is the character and weapon type I’ve indicated.  
![][image5]

9. Copy and paste the output.txt file into the **gcsim folder**, taking care to **remove the \[  \_output  \] in the name**  
10. Copy and paste the contents from the output folder in Athena’s folder into the config folder in the gcsim folder  
11. Open the Terminal in the gcsim folder and run **\[  python runbatch.py  \]**  
    * The name of the CSV file is irrelevant; name it as you want

Here is the command run in the Terminal of the **gcsim folder**:  
![][image6]

If everything is done correctly, within 30s the first optimized sim should load in your browser, soon to be followed by all the rest.

## **Troubleshooting**

1. If something indicates that **no such file exists**, recheck that your file name matches the command you are typing OR that you are running the command in the correct folder’s Terminal.

![][image7]

2. If **Python appears to not exist**, go to Settings and search **Manage App Execution Aliases**. Python and Python3 are both titled as “App Installer”. Turn off Python3 and rerun Terminal.

![][image8]
